<section id="auspicious">
  <h2>Auspicious Sectors in 2026</h2>

  <h3>Northwest — Star 8 (Wealth)</h3>
  <p>Star 8 (<span class="chinese-char">左輔</span>) is the <strong>current wealth star</strong> of Period 9 (the current 20-year feng shui period running from 2024 to 2043). In the Northwest in 2026, it brings strong financial and career energy. <strong>Activate this sector</strong> with moving water (a small fountain), bright lighting, and regular human activity. If your main door, office, or bedroom is in the Northwest, expect enhanced wealth opportunities. The star's Earth element is supported by Fire (the year's dominant element), making this an especially potent wealth sector in 2026.</p>

  <h3>Northeast — Star 1 (Career)</h3>
  <p>Star 1 (<span class="chinese-char">貪狼</span>) is the career and intelligence star. Its Water element in the Northeast creates a useful presence for study, career advancement, and strategic planning. <strong>Activate</strong> with a water feature, blue or black decor accents, and good lighting. Students and professionals seeking advancement should spend time in this sector.</p>

  <h3>West — Star 9 (Future Prosperity)</h3>
  <p>Star 9 (<span class="chinese-char">右弼</span>) represents future prosperity, celebrations, and happy events (weddings, births, promotions). In the West for 2026, this Fire star is strong in the Fire Horse year. <strong>Activate</strong> with candles, red accents, or purple decor. This is an excellent sector for social gatherings and celebration planning.</p>

  <h3>North — Star 6 (Authority)</h3>
  <p>Star 6 (<span class="chinese-char">武曲</span>) carries Metal energy associated with authority, discipline, and unexpected windfalls. In the North (Water sector), Metal produces Water — a productive relationship. This sector favors those in leadership, military, law enforcement, or government roles. Place metal objects here to strengthen.</p>
</section>

<section id="afflicted">
  <h2>Afflicted Sectors in 2026</h2>

  <h3>East — Star 5 (Five Yellow)</h3>
  <p>The Five Yellow (<span class="chinese-char">五黃煞</span>, Wu Huang Sha) is the most feared annual star. An Earth-element affliction star, it brings misfortune, accidents, illness, and obstacles to whatever sector it occupies. In 2026, it lands in the <strong>East</strong>.</p>
  <p><strong>Remedies:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Place a <strong>metal wu lou</strong> (gourd) or <strong>six-rod metal wind chime</strong> in the East — Metal exhausts Earth, weakening the Five Yellow</li>
    <li>Hang a <strong>string of six Chinese coins</strong> — six is the Metal number in the Hetu system</li>
    <li><strong>Avoid red, orange, and candles</strong> in the East — Fire produces Earth, which would strengthen the Five Yellow</li>
    <li><strong>Do not renovate, dig, or create loud disturbances</strong> in the East sector throughout 2026</li>
    <li>Keep this sector <strong>quiet and still</strong> — avoid placing the TV, stereo, or exercise equipment here</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Center — Star 2 (Illness)</h3>
  <p>Star 2 (<span class="chinese-char">巨門</span>) is the illness star, carrying Earth energy that manifests as physical ailments, chronic conditions, and health setbacks. Landing in the Center of the grid, it affects the entire home.</p>
  <p><strong>Remedies:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Place a <strong>brass or copper wu lou</strong> in the center of the home</li>
    <li>Avoid <strong>yellow and brown</strong> color schemes in the central area (these strengthen Earth)</li>
    <li>Add <strong>Metal-element cures</strong>: metal bowls, metal sculpture, or a metal singing bowl</li>
    <li>Keep the center of the home <strong>clean and well-ventilated</strong></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Southwest — Star 3 (Conflict)</h3>
  <p>Star 3 (<span class="chinese-char">祿存</span>) is the quarrelsome star. Its Wood energy in the Southwest (Earth sector) creates a Wood-controlling-Earth dynamic that manifests as disputes, legal troubles, and arguments among family members or business partners.</p>
  <p><strong>Remedies:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Place <strong>red or Fire-element items</strong> in the Southwest — Fire exhausts Wood and produces Earth, simultaneously weakening the affliction and strengthening the sector</li>
    <li>A <strong>red lamp, red rug, or red-toned artwork</strong> works well</li>
    <li>Avoid <strong>Water features</strong> in the Southwest (Water feeds Wood, strengthening the conflict star)</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section id="tai-sui">
  <h2>Tai Sui and Three Killings</h2>

  <h3>Tai Sui (<span class="chinese-char">太歲</span>) — South</h3>
  <p>The Tai Sui (Grand Duke Jupiter) resides in the direction of the year's zodiac animal. In 2026, the <a href="/zodiac/">Horse</a> occupies the <strong>South</strong> (specifically 172.5°–202.5°). The cardinal rule: <strong>do not confront the Tai Sui</strong>. This means:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Do not renovate, dig, or demolish</strong> in the South sector of your property</li>
    <li><strong>Do not sit facing South</strong> directly (facing the Tai Sui is confrontational)</li>
    <li><strong>Do sit with the South behind you</strong> (having the Tai Sui at your back provides its authority as support)</li>
  </ul>

  <p>The <em>Xieli Pian</em> (<span class="chinese-char">協紀辨方書</span>) prescribes that "one may lean upon the Tai Sui but must never face it in opposition." For those whose main door faces South, no special remedy is needed for normal daily use — the prohibition applies to construction and renovation, not to passage.</p>

  <h3>Sui Po (<span class="chinese-char">歲破</span>) — North</h3>
  <p>The Sui Po (Year Breaker) occupies the direction directly opposite the Tai Sui — the <strong>North</strong> in 2026. Similar restrictions apply: avoid renovations and ground-breaking in the North sector.</p>

  <h3>Three Killings (<span class="chinese-char">三煞</span>) — North</h3>
  <p>In Horse years, the Three Killings affliction occupies the <strong>North</strong> (specifically the full North sector from 337.5° to 22.5°). The Three Killings can be confronted (you may face North) but must not be behind you. <strong>Do not sit with your back to the North</strong> in 2026.</p>
</section>

