<section id="fire-element">
  <h2>Balancing Fire Element Energy in 2026</h2>
  <p>The Fire Horse year's dominant Fire energy amplifies the effects of Fire-related stars (Star 9) and creates additional considerations for <a href="/wuxing/">Earth-element</a> affliction stars (Stars 2 and 5), since Fire produces Earth in the productive cycle. This means the illness and Five Yellow stars are <em>indirectly strengthened</em> by the year's Fire energy.</p>

  <p>General Fire-year feng shui principles:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Metal cures are more important than usual</strong> — Metal exhausts the Earth stars that Fire strengthens. Increase Metal presence in afflicted sectors.</li>
    <li><strong>Water features provide needed balance</strong> — Water controls Fire and is excellent in the Northwest (Star 8) and Northeast (Star 1). Avoid Water in the East (would generate Wood, then Fire, then Earth — indirectly strengthening Star 5).</li>
    <li><strong>Wood is powerful but requires placement care</strong> — Wood feeds Fire, which is beneficial in most sectors but dangerous in the East and Center where it could strengthen affliction stars via the Fire-Earth chain.</li>
    <li><strong>Earth is abundant</strong> — the year's Fire produces Earth naturally. Avoid adding more Earth (yellow, brown, ceramics, crystals) to the East and Center sectors.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>The guiding principle from the <em>Zangshu</em> (<span class="chinese-char">葬書</span>, Book of Burial): "Qi rides the wind and scatters; it is bounded by water and halts." In a Fire-dominant year, water and metal serve as the essential halting forces that prevent energy from scattering into destructive excess.</p>
</section>
